===Coverage===
{{See also|Social Security Organization (Iran)}}
The [[Iranian Constitution|constitution]] entitles Iranians to basic health care, and most receive subsidized prescription [[drugs]] and [[vaccination]] programs. An extensive network of public clinics offers basic care at low cost, and general and specialty hospitals operated by the [[Ministry of Health and Medical Education]] (MOHME) provide higher levels of care. In most large cities, well-to-do persons use private clinics and hospitals that charge high fees.<ref name='Iran'/> About 73% of all Iranian workers have [[health care]] and [[social security]] coverage.<ref name='Iran'/> In 2000, 94% of the population could access local health services, according to the [[World Health Organization|WHO]]. Access ranged from 86% in rural areas to 100% in urban areas.<ref name='Iran'/> Between 80% and 94% of the population could access affordable essential medicines in 1999.<ref name='Iran'/> Since 2009, a new government plan called "the comprehensive insurance plan" provides basic coverage to all Iranians.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.presstv.com/Program/160874.html |title=Press TV |publisher=Press TV |date=2011-01-18 |accessdate=2012-02-05}}</ref>

===Workforce===
{{see also|Education in Iran}}
[[File:NIOC dental care.jpg|thumb|Dental care facility in Iran]]
